                      <locus target="#167r"/> Asmat prayer against the evil eye
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a03">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#167v"/> Asmat prayer against the evil eye, Ṣälota Nǝdra, ጸሎተ፡ ንድራ፡
                      </desc>
                      </item>

                      <item xml:id="e01">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#ir(ecto)"/> scrawls, illegible
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e02">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#70v"/> The middle line of the psalms is indented from the fore edge margin. In addition, a symbol of a cross in a later hand marks the midpoint of the Psalter
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e03">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#110r #110v #111r #111v #112r #112v #113r #113v #114r #114v #115r #115v #116r #116v 117r"/> A later hand has added in ink the spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e04">
                      <desc>
                      Numbered quires: quires 2–15
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e05">
                      <desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#24v #51r #51v #56r #64v"/>, etc.);
                      and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#89r #123r #128r #132v"/>);
                      and in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#138r"/>, line 7);
                      erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#125v"/>); text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#10r #25v #30r"/>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e06">
                      <desc>
                      The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection
                      of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe reduces the font size
                      at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (throughout). This scribe also will complete the line of text above or below the end of the line
                      (e.g., <locus target="#7v #73r"/>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>


                    </list>
